is the case.</li>\r\n	<li dir="LTR" style="line-height: 20.8px;">They can pay compensation only for financial loss and there are&nbsp;<a href="http://www.fscs.org.uk/what-we-cover/eligibility-rules/compensation-limits/">limits to the amounts of compensation they&nbsp;can pay</a>.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li dir="LTR" style="line-height: 20.8px;"><strong>For protected deposits</strong>: 100% of the first &pound;85,000 of the claim. This is the sterling equivalent of the &euro;100,000 deposit compensation limit applying to deposit takers within the EEA.</li>\r\n	<li dir="LTR" style="line-height: 20.8px;"><strong>For protected investment business</strong>, - 100% of the first &pound;50,000 of the claim.</li>\r\n	<li dir="LTR" style="line-height: 20.8px;">The FSCS was set up mainly to assist private individuals, although smaller businesses are also covered.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p class="notice">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<!--#funDetails--></div>\r\n<!--.clearfix-->', 7, '2016-05-08 08:43:49', '2016-05-22 09:29:35');
